Reference

IO for Actigraph Monitors

Functions for importing and exporting data with Actigraph Monitors (e.g. GT3X, GT9X)

export_actigraph_raw()

Export to Actigraph raw csv files

import_actigraph_count() import_actigraph_count_vm()

Import and convert Actigraph count csv files and load into data frame as in mhealth format.

import_actigraph_meta()

parse actigraph csv header to get related version and sampling rate information

import_actigraph_raw()

Import and convert Actigraph raw csv files and load into data frame as in mhealth format.

IO for ActivPal Monitors

Functions for importing and exporting data with ActivPal Monitors (e.g. ActivPal 3)

import_activpal_raw()

Import ActivPal Raw data files and load into dataframe as mhealth format.

API for computing MIMS-unit

Function to generate MIMS-unit value

mims_unit()

Compute activity counts using [citation] algorithm

APIs for Intermediate step

Functions used in intermediate process when computing MIMS-unit

interpolate()

Interpolate the missing points and unify sampling interval for the input sensor data

average_removal()

Apply average removal FIR filter to the input sensor data frame each column over certain breaks (e.g. hour, sec, min and etc.)

iir()

Apply iir filter to the input sensor data frame each column over a certain break (e.g. hour, sec, min and etc.).

bessel()

Apply low pass bessel filter to the input sensor data frame each column over certain breaks (e.g. hour, sec, min and etc.)

extrapolate.data.frame() extrapolate()

Apply extrapolate algorithm to a single stream of data.

aggregate()

Calculate summary value (area under curve) for each column over a certain break (e.g. hour, min).

Util functions

Utility functions

sampling_rate()

Get sensor data's sampling rate from the time difference of adjacent samples

extrapolate_rate()

compute extrapolation rate
